<title>FRANCE: Lagardere raises convertible bond issue.</title>
<headline>Lagardere raises convertible bond issue.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Lagardere Groupe said in a statement on Friday that it had increased to 5.5 billion francs, from five billion, the amount of convertibe bonds it would issue if the state allowed it to buy a 58-percent stake in Thomson-CSF.</p>
<p>The bonds, of which the issue is guaranteed by Credit Lyonnais and Dresdner Kleinwort Benson, will be convertibe in Thomson-CSF shares.</p>
<p>Lagardere said it had taken the decision on the basis of the high demand for the paper.</p>
